Jeb Bush departs after speaking at a rally Wednesday at Summerville Country Club in Summerville, S.C. (Andrew Harnik/AP)

SUMMERVILLE, S.C. — He's stuck in the polls and just lost a major endorsement. And now voters are in open panic about the fate of Jeb Bush.

The Republican presidential candidate faced a barrage of conflicting advice from supporters increasingly distressed by the rise of GOP front-runner Donald Trump and concerned that the former Florida governor's campaign has stalled.
